			<name>
				<baseName xml:lang="en">Waste rubber</baseName>
				<baseName xml:lang="zh">废旧橡胶</baseName>
			</name>
			<common:synonyms xml:lang="en">Waste tire; Old tires; Vulcanized rubbers</common:synonyms>
			<common:synonyms xml:lang="zh">Waste tire; Old tires; Vulcanized rubbers</common:synonyms>
			<classificationInformation>
				<common:classification name="ILCD 1.1" classes="../ILCDClassification.xml">
					<common:class level="0">Wastes</common:class>
					<common:class level="1">Construction waste</common:class>
				</common:classification>
			</classificationInformation>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Waste rubber, predominantly sourced from rubber tires of automobiles, trucks, and motorcycles, is a significant environmental issue due to its durability and large volume. Other sources include clothing, footwear, and miscellaneous durable and nondurable products. The disposal of waste rubber is challenging as the material takes several years to degrade. Vulcanized rubbers, a type of waste rubber, are extensively used in various applications due to their mechanical strength and durability. However, recycling waste rubber is difficult due to its durability, large volume, and the hazards involved in its handling and storage.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">废橡胶主要来自汽车、卡车和摩托车的橡胶轮胎，由于其耐用性和体积大，是一个重大的环境问题。其他来源包括服装、鞋类以及各种耐用和非耐用产品。废橡胶的处理具有挑战性，因为这种材料需要数年时间才能降解。硫化橡胶是一种废橡胶，由于其机械强度和耐久性，被广泛用于各种应用。然而，由于废橡胶的耐用性、体积大以及处理和储存所涉及的危险，回收废橡胶是困难的。</common:generalComment>
